    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Religious Studies              : Survey of women's involvement in the Christian tradition. Topics include feminist interpretation of scripture, ideas of virginity, marriage and motherhood, mysticism, asceticisms, European witchhunts, contemporary women's liberation theories.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Lucille Marr (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>Core course for the Women's Studies Minor program</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/relg-340" class="program-course-title">
